                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.20 Missions/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-03T16:00:00+03:06"
                            >May 3, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 4—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. Department’s 80, May 1, 5 p.m.<note n="97" xml:id="d764fn97">See footnote
                        94, above.</note> Colonel Garret B. Shomber was presented to King April 23
                    as chief of United States military <pb facs="0710" n="698" xml:id="pg_698"/>
                    mission. I fear grave weakening of American standing and influence with King Ibn
                    Saud if United States mission now withdrawn and British-led mission replaces it.
                    If Department intends effectively to defend oil reserves here such
                    considerations cannot be ignored.</p>
                <p>The King in discussing military mission never indicated any preference for Moslem
                    instructors. Please confirm that Department wishes me in concert with British
                    Minister to obtain King’s consent in change in mission.</p>
                <p>Because of overwhelming American economic interests in Saudi Arabia, British
                    should recognize American priority in economic and financial missions’ advisers
                    and experts without necessity of bargaining.</p>
                <p>Code text to Cairo airmail for Giles.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
